'''Feza Gürsey Institute''' ({{lang-tr|Feza Gürsey Enstitüsü}}) is a joint institute of [[Boğaziçi University]] and [[TÜBİTAK|TÜBİTAK (Scientific and Technological Research Council of Turkey)]] on [[physics]] research, founded in 1983 by [[Erdal İnönü]] with the name ''Research Institute for Basic Sciences''. It now continues as the ''Feza Gürsey Institute'', having been renamed in honor of [[Feza Gürsey]], a distinguished [[Turkish people|Turkish]] physicist. The institute is located within the Kandilli Campus of the [[Boğaziçi University]] in [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]. Currently it hosts researchers in [[mathematics]] and [[theoretical physics]].

